<br>
From a loving, compassionate boy... to a feral child, nothing but raw emotion and natural needs... to this apathatic-faced, remorseless killer, with burning passion in his eyes.<br>
<br>
It was all their fault.  The Koada`Dal.  That rare Teir`Dal was the product of two rare parents, hatred having no place in their hearts.  Then General Jyleel came, with other High Elf raiders, and the boy's parents were slain.  He killed for the first time that day, and he enjoyed it.<br>
<br>
Ironic, that a being with no hate in his soul was twisted into the Prince of Hate's greatest paradigm by the hatred of those who sought to remove a force that, without his childish ignorace, would've apalled the young Dark Elf.<br>
<br>
Now he is a Master of that force.<br>
<br>
Is Innoruuk truly evil, are the High Elves right?  This thought does not even occur to him.  For Tunare and Mithaniel and Erolissi's champions destroyed all he held dear, and it was the Prince of Hate who brought sanity, purpose, and even love back into the his life.<br>
<br>
Love?  Indeed, for he has a woman he calls his dearest, special to him beyond all other things.  She worships Innoruuk also, as a priestess, and the two are bound by the passion of their single overwhelming purpose.<br>
<br>
To destroy those who cast their once-happy lives into oblivion.<br>
<br>
The High Elves.<br>
<br>
Tunare's followers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The enemy...</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
-Vaelis t'Lanshia,<br>
Shadow Knight of Innoruuk<br>
