<br>
&quot;Hello, there.  Welcome to my tavern.  What can I get for you?&quot; <p>Drixa<BR>
Barmaid of the Hero Heart Tavern<BR>
"Pull up a stool, here's an ale to wash the road dust from your throat, and tell me <I>allllllllll</I> about it..."
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umennelkir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mennelkir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/15/01 2:38:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lordsofdrakova.com/members/mennelkir/mennelkir2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hatred's Champion</span><hr size=1> The figure's elfin form is obscured by a light suit of chainmail, over which he wears a dark robe.  Hands are gloved, but obviously slender, and what the hood of his black garb doesn't hide of the man's face, a veil of the same fabric does.<br>
<br>
When he speaks, his voice is soft, but with a razor edge.  His Common is even and precise, but his inflection is overly harsh.  &quot;Wine.  Chilled, if you are capable of such.&quot;<br>
<br>
The oddly-garbed fellow slumps into the nearest empty chair after speaking, seemingly exhausted.<br>
<br>
--Vaelis t'Lanshia,<br>
Shadow Knight of Innoruuk<br>
Master of the Indigo Void <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udrixa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drixa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Barmaid</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/18/01 12:41:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hatred's Champion</span><hr size=1> Drixa pulls out the  wine bottle from the bottom of her case where she knows it's gotten the most benefit from the ice.  She bristles a bit at the hint of a suggestion that she can't offer whatever would make one of her customers comfortable.  She takes it as a matter of  pride that no matter what race enters her bar, it takes someone determined to be unhappy to leave without a pleasant time.  She poors the wine out into a crystal goblet normally reserved for weddings.  She wants to make sure that he is satisfied.<br>
<br>
&quot;Here is your wine, sir.  Would you like some food to go with it?  You look as if you may be tired from a journey.  Or I could also reserve a room for you to rest...&quot;<br>
<br>
She waits patiently to see how  she can make him comfortable... <p>Drixa<BR>
Barmaid of the Hero Heart Tavern<BR>
"Pull up a stool, here's an ale to wash the road dust from your throat, and tell me <I>allllllllll</I> about it..."
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umennelkir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mennelkir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/18/01 2:38:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lordsofdrakova.com/members/mennelkir/mennelkir2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hatred's Champion</span><hr size=1> Silence is the barmaid's reply for long moments, the dark stranger taking the wine without commenting on Drixa's choosing of such an elegant glass especially to placate him.  The man lifts the drink upwards, sliding it beneath his veil and tilting his head slightly, his features remaining concealed.  After a few sips' worth, the goblet is placed on his table, he turning to face the barmaid.<br>
<br>
His Common is, as before, precise.  The speaking is somewhat slow and deliberate, with a harsh inflection, but the dark-clad man does not stumble over any words.  Those which are mispronounced are said wrongly with the same lack of hesitation as those correctly spoken.<br>
<br>
&quot;You have nothing here I require, but for this drink and a brief respite.  The first is taken care of, and I needn't waste my time with a room when this table will suffice.&quot;<br>
<br>
Without so much as a 'thank you', the slender figure turns away from Drixa, relaxing in his chair.  The wine goes untouched.<br>
<br>
-Vaelis t'Lanshia,<br>
Shadow Knight of Innoruuk<br>
